{"ClientSettings":{"Pn":{"Cn":1,"St":0,"Qs":0,"Prod":"P"},"Sc":{"Cn":1,"St":0,"Qs":0,"Prod":"H"},"Qz":{"Cn":1,"St":0,"Qs":0,"Prod":"T"},"Ap":true,"Mute":true,"Lad":"2026-03-16T00:00:00Z","Iotd":0,"Gwb":0,"Tns":0,"Dft":null,"Mvs":0,"Flt":0,"Imp":1,"Tobn":0},"MediaContents":[{"ImageContent":{"Description":"This is the kind of landscape that makes maps feel suddenly more interesting. Evening settles quietly over Maligne Lake in Jasper National Park, Alberta. As temperatures drop, the surface stills, mirroring snow-dusted peaks that formed during the last Ice Age. Stretching about 22 kilometres, the lake owes its existence to glacial movement that carved the valley and left behind meltwater basins. Today, cold, oxygen-rich freshwater sustains ecosystems that include species such as lake trout and mountain whitefish. Boat cruises and paddling routes offer one of the best ways to view Spirit Island, the small but widely photographed landmark featured in the image.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.AuroraIsland_EN-CA8332911364_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.AuroraIsland_EN-CA8332911364_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Where stillness steals the show","Title":"Aurora over Spirit Island on Maligne Lake, Jasper National Park, Alberta","Copyright":"© Mumemories/istock/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/52.873398,-117.954308/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-CA&od=2&shading=flat&pp=52.873398,-117.954308;S9;Jasper National Park, Alberta&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260316_AuroraIsland\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Maligne+Lake+Canada&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260316_0400\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260316_AuroraIsland"},"Ssd":"20260316","Name":"AuroraIsland","Market":"EN-CA","Hash":"8332911364","FullDateString":"Mar. 16, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Spring break on Vancouver Island looks a little different. Here, the Pacific Rim Whale Festival celebrates the annual spring migration of thousands of grey whales as they pass close to the island's west coast. Created by local communities in the 1980s, the festival marks the whales' return north from breeding lagoons in Baja California, Mexico.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.PacificRimNP_EN-CA7886674430_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.PacificRimNP_EN-CA7886674430_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Passing through, making waves","Title":"Pacific Rim National Park Reserve, Vancouver Island","Copyright":"© EmilyNorton/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/49.068329,-125.753273/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-CA&od=2&shading=flat&pp=49.068329,-125.753273;S9;Pacific Rim National Park Reserve, Vancouver Island&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260315_PacificRimNP\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Pacific+Rim+Whale+Festival&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260315_0400\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260315_PacificRimNP"},"Ssd":"20260315","Name":"PacificRimNP","Market":"EN-CA","Hash":"7886674430","FullDateString":"Mar. 15, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Long before pi had a name, people were drawn to its mystery. Every year on March 14, Pi Day highlights one of math's most recognisable constants. The date reflects the first three digits of pi (π), the ratio of a circle's circumference to its diameter: 3.14. Pi's infinite, nonrepeating decimal has fascinated thinkers for a long time. The modern celebration began in 1988, when physicist Larry Shaw marked the day with a fitting tribute: serving pie.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.CornwallDolmen_EN-CA7041540991_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.CornwallDolmen_EN-CA7041540991_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"An ancient angle on Pi","Title":"Lanyon Quoit, a Neolithic dolmen in Cornwall, England","Copyright":"© Helen Hotson/Alamy","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/50.147726,-5.599093/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-CA&od=2&shading=flat&pp=50.147726,-5.599093;S9;Lanyon Quoit, Cornwall, England&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260314_CornwallDolmen\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Pi+Day&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260314_0400\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260314_CornwallDolmen"},"Ssd":"20260314","Name":"CornwallDolmen","Market":"EN-CA","Hash":"7041540991","FullDateString":"Mar. 14, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Under the vaulted ceiling of Notre-Dame de Bon-Port in Les Sables-d'Olonne, a seaside town in western France, the stone ribs still guide the gaze upward. Construction of the soaring vaults began in 1646. The church—officially recognised as a French historic monument since 1993—stands on the site of a 13th-century chapel, a reminder of deep-rooted spiritual life on the Atlantic coast.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.VendeeVaults_EN-CA6633656389_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.VendeeVaults_EN-CA6633656389_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"A quiet masterpiece in stone","Title":"Vaults of the Church of Notre Dame de Bon-Port, Les Sables-d'Olonne, France","Copyright":"© Helmut Meyer zur Capellen/Alamy","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/46.496203,-1.786035/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-CA&od=2&shading=flat&pp=46.496203,-1.786035;S9;Notre Dame de Bon-Port, Les Sables-d'Olonne, France&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260313_VendeeVaults\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Notre+Dame+de+Bon+Port+Les-Sables+France&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260313_0400\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260313_VendeeVaults"},"Ssd":"20260313","Name":"VendeeVaults","Market":"EN-CA","Hash":"6633656389","FullDateString":"Mar. 13, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"High in Ecuador's cloud forests, a young sunbittern spreads its wings in an early display, casting flashes of orange, black and white through the filtered green light. The sudden contrast cuts through the moss‑covered branches and leaf‑shadowed understorey, offering a snapshot of the species' dramatic wing patterns. Adult sunbitterns most often show these bold markings during defensive displays, briefly transforming an elusive bird into a striking spectacle.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.SunbitternEcuador_EN-CA6009774194_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.SunbitternEcuador_EN-CA6009774194_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Wings in rehearsal","Title":"Juvenile sunbittern displaying at nest, Ecuador","Copyright":"© Andy Rouse/naturepl.com","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"The sunbittern's wings feature eye‑like patterns, often revealed during wing displays in low forest light.","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260312_SunbitternEcuador\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Sunbittern+bird&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260312_0400\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260312_SunbitternEcuador"},"Ssd":"20260312","Name":"SunbitternEcuador","Market":"EN-CA","Hash":"6009774194","FullDateString":"Mar. 12, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Spring hits differently in Cieza. It doesn't gently unfold—it erupts with colour. Between February and March, this small city in Spain's Murcia region is the epicentre of 'La Floración,' the flowering of peach trees. In a matter of days, more than 4,856 hectares—Spain's largest municipal peach production—transform into the sea of colour we see in today's image.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.PeachBloom_EN-CA5288839040_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.PeachBloom_EN-CA5288839040_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"A peachy keen spring","Title":"Peach trees in bloom, Cieza, Murcia, Spain","Copyright":"© Juan Maria Coy Vergara/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/38.239372,-1.418669/3?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-CA&od=2&shading=flat&pp=38.239372,-1.418669;S9;Cieza, Murcia, Spain&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260311_PeachBloom\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Cieza+Spain&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260311_0400\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260311_PeachBloom"},"Ssd":"20260311","Name":"PeachBloom","Market":"EN-CA","Hash":"5288839040","FullDateString":"Mar. 11, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Have you ever wondered what happens when fire, ice and time negotiate the same territory? Iceland's Hveravellir geothermal field has the answer. In this highland hotspot, energy from the Earth's interior meets the icy surface, triggering a volatile dialogue between pressure, temperature and stone. Fumaroles hiss, steam curls into the air and the ground paints itself with sulphur whites, rust reds and ochre yellows—not only artistry, but chemical reactions driven by extreme heat. In today's image, Bláhver, a natural hot spring, dazzles in electric blue. Its colour comes from mineral- and silica-rich waters that reflect light on the surface.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.SpringIceland_EN-CA4746064568_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.SpringIceland_EN-CA4746064568_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Fire under frost","Title":"Geothermal blue pool Bláhver at Hveravellir, Iceland","Copyright":"© Juan Maria Coy Vergara/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/64.865398,-19.559103/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-CA&od=2&shading=flat&pp=64.865398,-19.559103;S9;Hveravellir, Iceland&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260310_SpringIceland\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Blahver+pool+Iceland&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260310_0400\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260310_SpringIceland"},"Ssd":"20260310","Name":"SpringIceland","Market":"EN-CA","Hash":"4746064568","FullDateString":"Mar. 10, 2026"}],"PreloadMediaContents":[{"ImageContent":{"Description":"The strength of nature is nowhere more evident than in powerful storms. Scary? Yes. Fascinating? Even more so. Learning to understand and respect these forces helps humanity live more safely.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.SonoranStorm_EN-CA1002592145_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.SonoranStorm_EN-CA1002592145_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Guided by the weather","Title":"Lightning storm over saguaro cacti, Sonoran Desert, Arizona, United States","Copyright":"© Jack Dykinga/Nature Picture Library","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/32.248009,-112.91613/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-CA&od=2&shading=flat&pp=32.248009,-112.91613;S9;Sonoran Desert, Arizona&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260323_SonoranStorm\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=World+Meteorological+Day&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260323_0400\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260323_SonoranStorm"},"Ssd":"20260323","Name":"SonoranStorm","Market":"EN-CA","Hash":"1002592145","FullDateString":"Mar. 23, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Today is World Water Day, declared by the UN in 1992 and first observed the following year. Humanity could no longer drift along—we had to safeguard the very currents that keep us alive. Few places capture that urgency like Lake Tanganyika, in the Great Rift Valley of eastern Africa. From space, it's a 676-kilometre ribbon linking Tanzania, Burundi, the Democratic Republic of the Congo and Zambia. At the shoreline, it's a 10-million-year-old rift basin, formed as the Earth's crust slowly pulled apart.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.TanganyikaWater_EN-CA7392363187_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.TanganyikaWater_EN-CA7392363187_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"When water draws the line","Title":"Lake Tanganyika, Africa","Copyright":"© BEST-BACKGROUNDS/NASA/Shutterstock","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/-6.026425,29.475387/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-CA&od=2&shading=flat&pp=-6.026425,29.475387;S9;Lake Tanganyika, Africa&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260322_TanganyikaWater\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=World+Water+Day&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260322_0400\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260322_TanganyikaWater"},"Ssd":"20260322","Name":"TanganyikaWater","Market":"EN-CA","Hash":"7392363187","FullDateString":"Mar. 22, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"If Earth had a maintenance crew, forests would be spearheading it. They absorb carbon emissions, reduce soil erosion, safeguard biodiversity, influence rainfall and help maintain clean water supplies. They still cover about 31% of the world's land area, yet their continued decline shows how vulnerable these natural systems have become. Vast stretches continue to be cleared for agriculture, infrastructure and resource extraction, weakening ecosystems at an alarming rate.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.LeteaForest_EN-CA8565877542_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.LeteaForest_EN-CA8565877542_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Where roots run wild","Title":"Letea Forest, Danube Delta, Romania","Copyright":"© Wild Wonders of Europe/Widstrand/Nature Picture Library","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"The UN FAO estimates that about 10 million hectares of forest are cut down each year.","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260321_LeteaForest\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=International+Day+of+Forests&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260321_0400\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260321_LeteaForest"},"Ssd":"20260321","Name":"LeteaForest","Market":"EN-CA","Hash":"8565877542","FullDateString":"Mar. 21, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"A white snowdrop is spring's quiet debut. No confetti, no countdown—just a delicate flower appearing as the spring equinox balances day and night. Snowdrops are among the first to bloom, often pushing through cold soil before winter fully packs up. Their drooping, bell-shaped flowers may look delicate, but they're built for early arrival. Special antifreeze proteins in their cells help them tolerate frost, making them well suited to unpredictable late-winter weather.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.SpringSnowdrops_EN-CA7724863293_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.SpringSnowdrops_EN-CA7724863293_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"The quiet bloom of change","Title":"Snowdrops in spring","Copyright":"© klagyivik/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"Collectors crazy about snowdrops are called galanthophiles.","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260320_SpringSnowdrops\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=March+equinox&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260320_0400\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260320_SpringSnowdrops"},"Ssd":"20260320","Name":"SpringSnowdrops","Market":"EN-CA","Hash":"7724863293","FullDateString":"Mar. 20, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"An egg-laying mammal. No teeth. Reptilian gait. Built-in body armour. If the short-beaked echidna sounds like a checklist of contradictions, that's because it is—and it owns it. Native to Australia, Tasmania and parts of New Guinea, it's one of the few surviving monotremes, or mammals that lay eggs. Despite the headlines, it still qualifies as a mammal: it has fur, produces milk and is warm-blooded. The twist? Milk is released through specialised skin patches rather than nipples, leaving the young to lap it up.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.EchidnaAustralia_EN-CA1280925480_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.EchidnaAustralia_EN-CA1280925480_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Spike your curiosity","Title":"Short-beaked echidna, Adelaide Hills, Australia","Copyright":"© Etienne Littlefair/naturepl.com","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/-34.892811,138.836243/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-CA&od=2&shading=flat&pp=-34.892811,138.836243;S9;Adelaide Hills, South Australia&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260319_EchidnaAustralia\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Short-beaked+echidna&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260319_0400\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260319_EchidnaAustralia"},"Ssd":"20260319","Name":"EchidnaAustralia","Market":"EN-CA","Hash":"1280925480","FullDateString":"Mar. 19, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Tom McCall Waterfront Park, a roughly 14-hectare urban oasis along the Willamette River in Portland, Oregon, is one of the city's most beloved green spaces. Each spring—typically from mid-March to early April—it transforms into a sea of soft pink and white as cherry blossoms bloom. These vibrant trees along scenic walking paths offer a peaceful escape in the heart of the city. The park also features notable landmarks like Salmon Street Springs, an interactive fountain with numerous water jets and the Portland Saturday Market, a favourite local destination.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.PortlandBlossoms_EN-CA9305833993_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.PortlandBlossoms_EN-CA9305833993_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Urban blooms","Title":"Cherry blossoms at Tom McCall Waterfront Park, Portland, Oregon, United States","Copyright":"© Eric Vogt/Tandem Stills + Motion","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/45.522743,-122.669754/3?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-CA&od=2&shading=flat&pp=45.522743,-122.669754;S9;Tom McCall Waterfront Park, Portland, Oregon, USA&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260318_PortlandBlossoms\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Tom+McCall+Waterfront+Park&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260318_0400\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260318_PortlandBlossoms"},"Ssd":"20260318","Name":"PortlandBlossoms","Market":"EN-CA","Hash":"9305833993","FullDateString":"Mar. 18, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"St. Patrick, the patron saint of Ireland, was born in Roman Britain around the late 4th or early 5th century. According to legend, at 16, he was kidnapped by Irish raiders and brought to Ireland as a slave. After escaping, he returned home and later became a missionary, spreading Christianity across the island. He is famously associated, according to later tradition, with using the shamrock to explain the Holy Trinity. His legacy of faith has made St. Patrick's Day a global celebration.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.DonegalFort_EN-CA9009549230_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.DonegalFort_EN-CA9009549230_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Ireland's spiritual cros